author: pete
msg: fix a character encoding bug with multipart/form-data encoded forms:

the multipart upload request gets no character encoding since the browser does not send the content type. so we use the application encoding which we also demand for multipart forms using the form attribute "accept-encoding" = application encoding.
this should get us encoding-safe string in a multipart form.
problem encountered with jetty 6 and 7 on os x using firefox, safari + chrome
